data.title: U.S. Marine Sgt. Nathan Douglas, an explosive ordnance
data.meta_description: Download Image of U.S. Marine Sgt. Nathan Douglas, an explosive ordnance. Free for commercial use, no attribution required. U.S. Marine Sgt. Nathan Douglas, an explosive ordnance technician with Explosive Ordnance Disposal Detachment, Headquarters and Support Battalion, Marine Corps Installations West, Marine Corps Base Camp Pendleton, packs composition C-4 into a conical shaped charge during an explosive effects range at Range 108 on Marine Corps Base Camp Pendleton, California, Dec. 19, 2019. Camp Pendleton EOD technicians conduct these ranges in order to sustain and gain knowledge in the planning and destruction of large quantities of ammunition. Douglas is a native of Marshfield, Indiana. (U.S. Marine Corps photo by Lance Cpl. Alison Dostie). Dated: 19.12.2019.
